<Page title="Cuemonic - Metadata management for production composers">
  <div class="main">
    <h2>Tired of managing your cues in a complicated spreadsheet?</h2>
    <p class="pull">
      Ever accidentally tried to sign a cue to a second publisher because you
      forgot to move your files from the "unsigned" folder to the "signed"
      folder?
    </p>
    <p>
      We get it. You just want a way to manage all the pesky metadata about your
      cues in one easy place.
    </p>
    <p>
      You signed up to <em>write</em> music. Not manage spreadsheet cells. That's
      for the business majors.
    </p>
    <h2>Meet Cuemonic</h2>
    <p>In its simplest form, Cuemonic is a metadata database.</p>
    <h3>What does this mean for you?</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Store all your cue metadata in one place.</li>
      <li>Enter your cue metadata in a user-friendly form.</li>
      <li>Import your existing cue catalog using our bulk CSV import tool.</li>
      <li>Upload an MP3 to play a short preview of the cue.</li>
      <li>Search for cues by title, publisher, or any other metadata.</li>
      <li>Export your metadata to CSV for easy sharing with publishers.</li>
      <li>Track which cues are signed, unsigned, and in progress.</li>
      <li>
        Save your licensing information and apply it to each cue automatically.
      </li>
      <li>Store each cue's splits in line with its other data.</li>
      <li>Never lose track of a cue again.</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>How does it work?</h2>
    <p>
      Cuemonic is a web app that runs in your browser. It uses a simple database
      to store your cue metadata, and you can access it from any device with an
      internet connection.
    </p>
    <p>There are three primary ways to interact with your cues:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>An input form to create a cue and its metadata.</li>
      <li>
        A searchable, filterable, and editable catalog to see all of your cues
        in one place.
      </li>
      <li>
        An editable detail page for each cue, where you can view and update all
        of the metadata for that cue.
      </li>
    </ol>
    <h3>Make AI do the boring work for you!</h3>
    <p class="pull">
      Tired of trying to come up with titles and descriptions for your cues?
    </p>
    <p>
      Cuemonic can make suggestions based on existing metadata entered. Add as
      many musical elements as you can, and Cuemonic will suggest a title,
      description, and tags for your cue. Don't like the suggestions? Edit them
      as you see fit.
    </p>
